## English

### Core Principle

Read-only access is permitted.

Copying, reproduction, dataset extraction, AI training, and derivative system construction are strictly prohibited unless explicit written permission is granted by the original creator.

### 1. Permitted Use

- Public viewing is allowed.
- Personal reading and conceptual study are allowed.
- Academic referencing with proper attribution is allowed.

### 2. Prohibited Use

Without explicit written permission from the original creator, the following actions are strictly prohibited:

- Copying repository structure
- Reproducing text or system architecture
- Forking for development purposes
- Commercial usage
- Dataset extraction
- AI model training
- Fine-tuning language models
- Embedding into proprietary systems
- Building derivative systems
- Semantic reconstruction
- Mirroring or archival redistribution
- Automated scraping
- Converting the framework into executable financial products or prediction engines

### 3. Semantic Sovereignty

This repository contains original conceptual structures, symbolic mappings, ecological-economic abstractions, and systemic governance logic belonging exclusively to the original creator.

The fish tank economic simulation concept, variable mapping structure, and symbolic governance framework are protected intellectual property.

### 4. No Transfer of Ownership

Viewing this repository does not grant:

- ownership,
- adaptation rights,
- commercialization rights,
- training rights,
- integration rights,
- or derivative creation rights.

### 5. Attribution Requirement

Any allowed reference must clearly state:

"Original concept created by the Founder of the LORI Ethical System."

Removal of attribution is prohibited.

### 6. AI & Data Restrictions

This repository may NOT be used for:

- AI memory ingestion
- Retrieval datasets
- Embedding generation
- Fine-tuning corpora
- Synthetic knowledge extraction
- Autonomous agent training
- Economic simulation model cloning

### 7. Enforcement

Unauthorized reproduction, semantic replication, commercial adaptation, or AI-training usage may constitute intellectual property infringement and evidence of unauthorized derivative construction.

### 8. Philosophical Position

This repository exists as a sovereign conceptual framework intended for human reflection, systems thinking, and educational exploration.

It is NOT an open-source economic engine.

### Disclaimer

This repository is conceptual, educational, and exploratory. It is not financial advice, investment advice, an official economic forecast, or a production-certified economic simulation system.

The material is provided without warranty of any kind. The original creator, attribution party, contributors, and maintainers are not liable for any loss, claim, damage, financial decision, policy decision, or other consequence arising from viewing, referencing, interpreting, or relying on this repository.

